Package: ogrdbstats
Type: Package
Title: Analysis of Adaptive Immune Receptor Repertoire Genotype Statistics
Version: 0.5.0
Author: William Lees
Maintainer: William Lees <william@lees.org.uk>
Description: Multiple tools are now available for inferring the personalised 
    genotype from an Adaptive Immune Receptor Repertoire sequencing repertoire. 
    The package can read the output from a number of these tools, converting to 
    a standard format and supplementing with rich data such as usage and 
    characterisation of 'novel' germline alleles. These reports can be 
    particularly useful when considering the validity of novel inferences. Use
    of the information provided by ogrdbstats is described in Ohlin et al. 
    (2019) <doi:10.3389/fimmu.2019.00435>.
License: CC BY-SA 4.0
Encoding: UTF-8
